%I A193099 #15 Jun 10 2026 01:06:55
%S A193099 1,1,4,34,466,9044,230827,7388781,287044354,13212057907,707417718215,
%T A193099 43431362340153,3022050938855344,236053437141340206,
%U A193099 20532456001485751429,1975258248906891145913,208928124926501980596761,24172548454436633069025270
%N A193099 E.g.f. A(x) satisfies: A'(x) = 1 + A(A(A(A(x)))).
%H A193099 Paul D. Hanna, <a href="/A193099/b193099.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..200</a>
%F A193099 E.g.f. A(x) = Sum_{n>=1} a(n)*x^n/n! satisfies the following formulas, in which zero is the constant of integration where applicable.
%F A193099 (1) A'(x) = 1 + A^4(x).
%F A193099 (2) A(x) = x + Integral A^4(x) dx.
%F A193099 (3) A(x) = Series_Reversion( Integral 1/(1 + A^3(x)) dx ). - _Paul D. Hanna_, Jun 09 2026
%e A193099 E.g.f.: A(x) = x + x^2/2! + 4*x^3/3! + 34*x^4/4! + 466*x^5/5! + 9044*x^6/6! + ...
%e A193099 Related expansions.
%e A193099 The first few iterations of A(x) begin
%e A193099 A^2(x) = x + 2*x^2/2! + 11*x^3/3! + 111*x^4/4! + 1702*x^5/5! + 35854*x^6/6! + ...
%e A193099 A^3(x) = x + 3*x^2/2! + 21*x^3/3! + 249*x^4/4! + 4303*x^5/5! + 99650*x^6/6! + ...
%e A193099 A^4(x) = x + 4*x^2/2! + 34*x^3/3! + 466*x^4/4! + 9044*x^5/5! + ...
%o A193099 (PARI) {a(n) = my(A=x,B); for(k=1, n, A= truncate(A) + x*O(x^k); B = subst(A, x, A);
%o A193099 A = intformal(1 + subst(B,x,B)) +x*O(x^n)); n!*polcoef(EGF=A, n)}
%o A193099 {upto(n) = a(n); Vec(serlaplace(EGF))}
%o A193099 upto(25) \\ program revised by _Paul D. Hanna_, Jun 09 2026
